<div id="review_3072417122" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3072417122" />
    <a title="Janie Johnson" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5116650-janie-johnson"><img alt="Janie Johnson" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1486148700p2/5116650.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3072417122?book_show_action=true">Dec 04, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Janie Johnson" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Janie Johnson" href="/user/show/5116650-janie-johnson">Janie Johnson</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5116650-janie-johnson?shelf=2019">2019</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3072417122" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1693940570530214836">I wanted to read a Christmas book this year as I do every year, so I chose The Christmas Sweater. This book was based on true accounts of the author, although there were fictitious parts to the story as well. The story was a pretty awesome read, although it was highly predictable. I love how the story made me feel everything, every loss, every heartache, the happiness and the sadness. A very emotionally written story. I think that best part of the book were the lessons to be learned, such as &apos;li</span>
  <span id="freeText1693940570530214836" style="display:none">I wanted to read a Christmas book this year as I do every year, so I chose The Christmas Sweater. This book was based on true accounts of the author, although there were fictitious parts to the story as well. The story was a pretty awesome read, although it was highly predictable. I love how the story made me feel everything, every loss, every heartache, the happiness and the sadness. A very emotionally written story. I think that best part of the book were the lessons to be learned, such as 'life does not mold you, you mold your life.' Very good advice. So many great quotes to live by, great characters, definitely worth the read. </span>
  <a data-text-id="1693940570530214836" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


