<div id="review_40866719" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/40866719" />
    <a title="Ben" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/906534-ben"><img alt="Ben" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1212674844p2/906534.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/40866719?book_show_action=true">Dec 24, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ben" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ben" href="/user/show/906534-ben">Ben</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer40866719" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17152811614589452495">A phenomenal book. Glenn Beck takes the reader through his life and experiences he had that helped him discover many of the same lessons that we must all learn: 1.) Life is not fair. 2.) God wants us to be happy. 3.) While God wants us to be happy, whether or not we ARE happy depends entirely on how we live our life in comparison with those events which God sees fit to subject.<br/><br/>While some may not appreciate the obvious comparisons to the Gospel, the author uses the story to share how he came to k</span>
  <span id="freeText17152811614589452495" style="display:none">A phenomenal book. Glenn Beck takes the reader through his life and experiences he had that helped him discover many of the same lessons that we must all learn: 1.) Life is not fair. 2.) God wants us to be happy. 3.) While God wants us to be happy, whether or not we ARE happy depends entirely on how we live our life in comparison with those events which God sees fit to subject.<br /><br />While some may not appreciate the obvious comparisons to the Gospel, the author uses the story to share how he came to know Jesus Christ.<br /><br />The story revolves mostly around one Christmas when the main character "Eddie", later revealed as the author, who hopes with all his might to get the bike he loves for Christmas and, upon being denied the one gift he wanted more than any other, how his life encounters a very sudden turn of events after the nearly expected loss of his father to cancer and how his mother suddenly was taken from him as the result of a motor vehicle accident. This is a must read for everyone, regardless of whether they are affiliated with any religion or no religion.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17152811614589452495" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
