<div id="review_1479328177" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1479328177" />
    <a title="Joanna Mugglin" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/19546992-joanna-mugglin"><img alt="Joanna Mugglin" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1475005750p2/19546992.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1479328177?book_show_action=true">Dec 25, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Joanna Mugglin" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Joanna Mugglin" href="/user/show/19546992-joanna-mugglin">Joanna Mugglin</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/19546992-joanna-mugglin?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1479328177" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13333643887571866868">Wow. Just wow. A couple days ago, I couldn&apos;t have imagined my perspective revolutionizing so quickly. I picked this book up only because I wanted to read something related to this wonderful season; (I&apos;m sitting under the Christmas tree as I write this.) Little could I know how much of an impact this profound story would have on my heart. <br/><br/>The protagonist, twelve-year-old Eddie, due to his family&apos;s impoverished state, receives &quot;a stupid, handmade, ugly sweater&quot; for Christmas instead of a new bike.</span>
  <span id="freeText13333643887571866868" style="display:none">Wow. Just wow. A couple days ago, I couldn't have imagined my perspective revolutionizing so quickly. I picked this book up only because I wanted to read something related to this wonderful season; (I'm sitting under the Christmas tree as I write this.) Little could I know how much of an impact this profound story would have on my heart. <br /><br />The protagonist, twelve-year-old Eddie, due to his family's impoverished state, receives "a stupid, handmade, ugly sweater" for Christmas instead of a new bike. Crushed, he vents his frustration and anger on his mother and grandparents. Through several awful, more unexpected events, Eddie falls farther and farther away. He reaches the absolute depths of despair. What starts as an innocent and simple Christmas lesson of contentment turns into a new outlook on the important things in life and a reminder that no matter how far you drift, the Lord will restore you if you allow Him. <br /><br />I have to admit several parts moved me to tears, and I will forever cherish this story.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13333643887571866868" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


